webpackJsonp([2238],{"./node_modules/json-loader/index.js!./.cache/json/articles-certificates-convert-celsius-to-fahrenheit.json":function(e,o){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p><img src="https://forum.freecodecamp.com/images/emoji/emoji_one/triangular_flag_on_post.png?v=3" alt=":triangular_flag_on_post:" title=":triangular_flag_on_post:"> Remember to use <a><strong><code>Read-Search-Ask</code></strong></a> if you get stuck. Try to pair program <img src="https://forum.freecodecamp.com/images/emoji/emoji_one/busts_in_silhouette.png?v=3" alt=":busts_in_silhouette:" title=":busts_in_silhouette:"> and write your own code <img src="https://forum.freecodecamp.com/images/emoji/emoji_one/pencil.png?v=3" alt=":pencil:" title=":pencil:"></p>\n<h3><img src="https://forum.freecodecamp.com/images/emoji/emoji_one/checkered_flag.png?v=3" alt=":checkered_flag:" title=":checkered_flag:"> Problem Explanation:</h3>\n<p>The algorithm to convert from Celsius to Fahrenheit is the temperature in Celsius times <code>9/5</code>, plus <code>32</code>.</p>\n<p>You are given a variable <strong>celsius</strong> representing a temperature in Celsius. Use the variable <strong>fahrenheit</strong> already defined and apply the algorithm to assign it the corresponding temperature in Fahrenheit.</p>\n<h4>Relevant Links</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="http://www.purplemath.com/modules/orderops.htm">The Order of Operations: PEMDAS</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://www.khanacademy.org/math/pre-algebra/order-of-operations/order_of_operations/v/order-of-operations">Order of Operation: Video</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><img src="https://forum.freecodecamp.com/images/emoji/emoji_one/speech_balloon.png?v=3" alt=":speech_balloon:" title=":speech_balloon:"> Hint: 1</h2>\n<p>Take a look at the code. There is an area that you\'re not supposed to edit. From there, ask yourself - what is used there that I haven\'t seen before?</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>try to solve the problem now</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><img src="https://forum.freecodecamp.com/images/emoji/emoji_one/speech_balloon.png?v=3" alt=":speech_balloon:" title=":speech_balloon:"> Hint: 2</h2>\n<p>Keep in mind the <strong>order of operation</strong> check the link in the <em>links</em> section for more information.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>try to solve the problem now</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Spoiler Alert!</h2>\n<p><img src="//discourse-user-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/original/2X/2/2d6c412a50797771301e7ceabd554cef4edcd74d.gif" alt="687474703a2f2f7777772e796f75726472756d2e636f6d2f796f75726472756d2f696d616765732f323030372f31302f31302f7265645f7761726e696e675f7369676e5f322e676966.gif"></p>\n<p><strong>Solution ahead!</strong></p>\n<h2><img src="https://forum.freecodecamp.com/images/emoji/emoji_one/beginner.png?v=3" alt=":beginner:" title=":beginner:"> Basic Code Solution:</h2>\n<pre><code>function convertToF(celsius) {\n  // Only change code below this line\n  var fahrenheit = (celsius * (9/5)) + 32;\n\n  // Only change code above this line\n  if ( typeof fahrenheit !== \'undefined\' ) {\n  return fahrenheit;\n  } else {\n    return \'fahrenheit not defined\';\n  }\n}\n\n// Change the inputs below to test your code\nconvertToF(30);\n</code></pre>\n<h3>Code Explanation:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Declare the <strong>fahrenheit</strong> variable.</li>\n<li>Make sure the proper order of arithmetic operations is followed by using parenthesis (<code>()</code>) when needed.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><img src="https://forum.freecodecamp.com/images/emoji/emoji_one/clipboard.png?v=3" alt=":clipboard:" title=":clipboard:"> NOTES FOR CONTRIBUTIONS:</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><img src="https://forum.freecodecamp.com/images/emoji/emoji_one/warning.png?v=3" alt=":warning:" title=":warning:"> <strong>DO NOT</strong> add solutions that are similar to any existing solutions. If you think it is <strong><em>similar but better</em></strong>, then try to merge (or replace) the existing similar solution.</li>\n<li>Add an explanation of your solution.</li>\n<li>Categorize the solution in one of the following categories â€” <strong>Basic</strong>, <strong>Intermediate</strong> and <strong>Advanced</strong>. <img src="https://forum.freecodecamp.com/images/emoji/emoji_one/traffic_light.png?v=3" alt=":traffic_light:" title=":traffic_light:"></li>\n<li>Please add your username only if you have added any <strong>relevant main contents</strong>. (<img src="https://forum.freecodecamp.com/images/emoji/emoji_one/warning.png?v=3" alt=":warning:" title=":warning:"> <strong><em>DO NOT</em></strong> <em>remove any existing usernames</em>)</li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote>\n<p>See <img src="https://forum.freecodecamp.com/images/emoji/emoji_one/point_right.png?v=3" alt=":point_right:" title=":point_right:"> <a href="http://forum.freecodecamp.com/t/algorithm-article-template/14272"><strong><code>Wiki Challenge Solution Template</code></strong></a> for reference.</p>\n</blockquote>',frontmatter:{title:"Convert Celsius to Fahrenheit",parent:"/home/stuart/guides/src/pages/articles/certificates/convert-celsius-to-fahrenheit/index.md absPath of file"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/articles/certificates/convert-celsius-to-fahrenheit/"}}}});
